In 1997, Boeing merged with McDonnell Douglas,
a move（） that some say marked the beginning of the end.

It's been said that "McDonnel Douglas bought Boeing with Boeing's money,"
ushering（） in a new era where profit trumped（） engineering excellence.
1997年，波音与麦道公司合并，一些人认为这标志着末日的开始。有人说“麦道公司用波音的钱收购了波音”，引领了一个新时代，利润凌驾于工程卓越之上。


The new management（） made it clear:
Boeing was no longer just an engineering company;
it was a profit-driven（） business.

Headquarters were shifted（） to Chicago,
effectively silencing（） the voices of engineers in crucial decision-making processes.
新管理层明确表示：波音不再仅仅是一家工程公司；它是一家以利润为驱动的企业。总部迁至芝加哥，有效地压制了工程师在关键决策过程中的声音。

The aftermath（） of the merger
saw Airbus surpassing（） Boeing's market share in 2003.

And in 2010, Airbus dealt（） another blow with the release of the A320neo,
a plane that boasted（） 6% less fuel consumption than Boeing's 737NG.
合并后的后果是空客在2003年超越了波音的市场份额。
而在2010年，空客发布了A320neo，这款飞机比波音的737NG燃油消耗少了6％

In response, Boeing rushed（） to launch（） the 737 Max in 2011,
boasting fuel-efficient engines and promising enhanced performance.
But beneath the sleek（） exterior lay a fatal flaw.
作为回应，波音于2011年急忙推出了737 Max，宣称拥有燃油效率高的发动机，并承诺性能更强。但在光鲜的外表下隐藏着一个致命的缺陷。

Two catastrophic crashes（）, Lion Air Flight 610 and Ethiopian Airlines Flight 302,
shook（） the world's trust in Boeing.

Investigations revealed（） a deadly flaw in the MCAS,
a flight stabilizing software designed to
counteract（） the aircraft's tendency to pitch up（）.
两起灾难性坠机事件，印尼狮航610航班和埃塞俄比亚航空302航班，动摇了世界对波音的信任。调查揭示了MCAS中的致命缺陷，这是一款旨在抵消飞机俯仰趋势的飞行稳定软件

MCAS（调整飞机仰角的软件）
comment👇
波音隐藏了这款软件的存在，为了省去培训飞行员的培训费用
multiple teams makes white lies for spending less money, add them all together, the issue get to reveal itself.
that is, a perfect storm.

MCAS was supposed to enhance safety, but it ended up becoming a ticking time bomb（）.
Boeing's rush to compete led to corners being cut（）, and lives were lost as a result.
本应增强安全性，但最终变成了一个定时炸弹。波音为了竞争，赶工而成，结果导致了生命的损失
